simulator.framework

Interface TimeSensitive

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractInterval, BERFaultModel, BlackoutFaultModel, CANNetwork, CarButtonLight, CarWeightSensor, Controller, DoorMotor, DoorReversalSensor, DriveControl, DriveObject, FaultInjector, HallButtonLight, Interval, MessageInjector, NetworkScheduler, NetworkScheduler.Connection.RepeatedPayload, NetworkUtilization, PassengerInjector, PhysicalNetwork, PhysicalNetwork.EventPrinter, PhysicalNetwork.EventSender, ProgressLogger, RuntimeMonitor, Safety, SampleDispatcherMonitor, SamplePerformanceMonitor

    public interface TimeSensitive
    Allows simulator components to execute at specified time intervals. Classes that want to act as handlers for Timer objects must implement this interface.
    See Also:
    AbstractTimer, Timer, SystemTimer
